(19, 'You are finally back in your room and can''t wait to', 'Consider a ladder of length 10 m. force F(g) pulls down from center of the ladder. If the ladder weighing 5 kg is 30 degree above the horizontal ground. Find F(g) .', '50', 'Try Sliding Down the Plumbing Line', 'Take the Lift', 'Take Stairs', 'corridr.jpg'),
(20, 'You decide to take the lift and start frantically ', 'A block of weight(W) hanging from the ceiling of a stationary elevator through a spring. The cable breaks and the elevator starts falling freely. What kind of motion does the block experience?', 'Simple Harmonic Motion', '', '', '', 'lift.jpg'),
(21, 'You look around the corridor and it is unusually qu', 'This is code for a 5-letter word, and is named after a famous English philosopher, scientist, author and mathematician.AABBBAABAAABABBABABBABBBA. Name the person after whom this is named.', 'Francis Bacon', '', '', '', 'strs.jpg'),
(22, 'Sometimes in life, you need to do things you?d nev', 'Consider that the observation deck of a tall building is 370 m above the ground. Determine the time required for a coin to free fall from the deck to the ground below.', '8.69', 'Poornima', 'Timmys', 'Annapoorna 2nd Floor', 'def.jpg'),
(23, 'You go to Timmys looking for food , but find out ', 'Consider you have 3 bags. The first bag has 2 red balls, second bag has 2 blue balls, third bag has one red and one blue ball. All the bags are labelled but the labels are all wrong. You are allowed to select one bag, pick one rock at random , see its color and put it back in the bag, without seeing the color of the other rock. How many such operations are needed to correct the labels of the bag?A- 3 operations B- just one C- cannot be determined D- 6 operations', 'B', '', '', '', 'def.jpg'),
(24, 'You have always been curious about the locked room', 'What can you put in a wooden box that will make it lighter. The more you put, the lighter it gets yet the box remains empty.', 'Holes', '', '', '', 'def.jpg'),
