(37, 'You look around, clenching your bag close to you -', 'A bus driver is driving a bus with a constant <br>velocity of (v), the driver slams on the brakes. <br>The truck stops after travelling the distance (d).<br>If the driver had been travelling with twice the <br>velocity, what would be the stopping distance? <br>(compared to the first trial.) _______ ', '4', 'UDUPI BUS STAND', 'A BUS BOUND TO MANGALORE', 'AN EMPTY BUS PARKED ACROSS THE STREET', 'def.jpg'),
